The paper proposes a deep learning-based anomaly detection model, which is likely to fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The model is also designed to detect anomalies in transportation networks, which could fall under the category of computer networks and security (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
